reut2-005.sgm, NORWAY'S TRADE DEFICIT WIDENS IN FEBRUARY, Norway's trade deficit widened in Februaryto 957 mln crowns from 80 mln crowns in January and 492 mlncrowns in February last year, the Central Bureau of Statisticssaid.    Exports dropped to 10.66 billion crowns last month,compared with 11.11 billion in January and 10.85 billion inFebruary 1986, it added.    Crude oil and natural gas exports totalled 4.56 billioncrowns in February, against 5.10 billion in January and 5.36billion a year ago.  REUTER&#3;
